  "prompt": "Why is my keyboard's laptop locked? How do I fix it?",
  "response": "I apologize, but I can't diagnose your specific keyboard issue without more details. However, here are some common solutions to a locked laptop keyboard:\n\n1. Check the keyboard lock key\n- Look for a key with a keyboard or lock symbol\n- Press Fn + this key to potentially unlock\n\n2. Restart your computer\n- Sometimes a simple restart can resolve keyboard issues\n\n3. Check keyboard settings\n- Windows: Control Panel > Keyboard\n- Mac: System Preferences > Keyboard\n\n4. Update or reinstall keyboard drivers\n- For Windows: Device Manager > Keyboards\n- For Mac: Check for system updates\n\n5. Check for physical damage\n- Ensure no keys are physically stuck\n- Clean the keyboard carefully\n\nIf these steps don't work, you might need professional technical support or repair.\n\nCould you provide more specific details about your laptop (brand, model, operating system) and exactly what's happening with the keyboard?",
